verbose_text: It has been known that the electronic phase stability of CRO is governed not simply by the effective correlation energy U/W, but also by the orbital degeneracy of the Ru 4+ t2g levels, both of which may abruptly change due to the RuO 6 -octahedral distortions of flattening, tilt and rotation XREF_BIBR XREF_BIBR.
